Johnson and Johnson said the U.S.Food and Drug Administration has notified the company its foodadditive petition for a high-intensity sweetener has beenformally accepted and now will be reviewed by the agency.    The company said the product, with the generic name ofsucralose, is made from sugar and tastes like sugar, but isabout 600 times sweeter.    It yields no calories and does not promote tooth decay. Reuter&#3;